				lol people are amazing. I cant believe there are people out there who make it sound as if EQ/MMORPG's are life. Take a rag wipe the dirt off and look out your window once in a while. Thats life you see out there. And thats not a flame cause i play EQ 8-12 hours a day at least twice a week but i also know when to draw the line between letting the game effect me in RP and letting it effect me in RL. If the game is seriously bugging you enough in real life (real life doesnt mean playing your main rather then an alt but actually viewing things here on Earth)you might need to seek some help seriously. Like a whole truckload of people have said before and will say for as long as MMORPG's are around &quot;It's just a GAME&quot;. Learn to cope. When some moron steals a kill from you in-game or makes fun of you in ooc give him/her a hard time in game and let it go. Some of you people sound like you sit there for days thinking about these stupid things that happen in-game. GMs are regular everyday people like me and you they have a job to do if the event sucks oh well let it go. Dont write 8000 emails to Verant saying how much you were traumatized by how terrible the last GM event on Tribunal was because it sucked and the drops were worthless. Who cares its just a game. you play for the fun factor not for the once in a great while GM events. Ah well. As for inconsiderate and downright malicious people in-game i do agree they need to get the hammer dropped on them. Too many people get away with taunting another person in tells ooc etc and basically harassing them. Ive seen it and im sure anyone with a character over lvl 20 has seen it. Its just the way the game is. Until Verant decides to crack down on these types of people we all just need to learn how to use /ignore. Eh Ive rambled long enough. Good luck everyone and remember its just a game<BR>
 
