				Xott,<BR>
<BR>
I appreciate the attempt.  I agree with much of what you said, unfortunately(or fortunately) the many people have come in to demonstrate why this occurs in game.  The internet with all its benefits, also allows the anonymity the lowest and basest form of humans love so dearly.  These folks do not care if the cannot speak in written word with any coherence or intellect, because they are clearly beyond retribution.  They care little for the feelings of others, that is their perverted sense of &quot;freedom&quot;.  The asinine behaviors allowed by the social decay called &quot;moral relativism&quot; has them convinced that they are well within the bounds of &quot;acceptable&quot;, because they say so.  News Flash to those imbeciles that believe in the tenents of Moral relativism!!!! There is right and wrong!  There are things that are appropriate and things that are inapropriate.  As long as this game allows immature juveniles to do as they like without any fear of retribution, they will continue to do abhorent and inconsiderate acts.  Its like the rest of the internet, as long as noone know who you are, people will continue to do stupid things; like post  properly worded and articulate responses that are directed at a bunch of ape incapable of understanding it.  For those folks I say, All Xott is trying to do is introduce you to a concept that is obviously foreign to you, MANNERS.  Whether you want to play one way or another does not take away from the fact that one way is mannerly and polite, and the opposite is NOT!  Your anonymity does not strip away the bounds of polite interaction in a social situation, it only strips away the conventions that enforce these Social niceties.  You choosing to ignore them and act irresponsibly and childishly, is not right because you choose it.  It is not right because noone is there to stop you from doing it.  It is, quite frankly, NOT RIGHT.  Just because you want to do it, or you choose to play this way, does not make you any less wrong.  Yes this is only a game.  Yes this is for fun. Yes I play evil characters, and they do some pretty abhorent things, but they do not do things that hurt the fun of the people controlling the characters behind this game, and the inconsiderate and immature actions of which Xott is speaking do cause that type of harm.  All that being said there is no way to get through the low-brow, idiocy, nor the uncontrollable immaturity that makes up the web and this game.  As long as these sites and games house the undisciplined and unsupervised children (mentally and physically age challenged) of the world, we will continue to see this &quot;diverity&quot; of belief structure and behavior.  Now please flame on, and please use your best and basest language to prove my point.
